{{ 'dev-story-slider.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script src="{{ 'dev-story-slider.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>

{%- comment -%} Fixed design tokens from Figma — not merchant-controlled {%- endcomment -%}
<style>
  .story-slider {
    /* Brand params. The faces are loaded theme-wide by snippets/dev-brand-fonts.liquid; this
       only selects them. No --container-max: the track is deliberately full-bleed so tiles can
       scroll out past the right gutter — the only inset is --section-px. */
    --section-px: 64px;
    --section-px-m: 16px;

    /* Typography. Desktop/Title 3 -> Mobile/Title 3 (32 -> 24); the mobile artboard states its
       own size, so it wins over a scale factor. Captions are Body/Lg (18) -> Body/Md (16). */
    --font-heading-size: 32px;
    --font-heading-size-m: 24px;
    --font-heading-weight: 500;
    --font-heading-lh: 1.2;

    --font-body-size: 18px;
    --font-body-size-m: 16px;
    --font-body-weight: 500;
    --font-body-weight-bold: 700;
    --font-body-lh: 1.4;

    /* Rhythm. Desktop stacks heading / track / controls at 32; the mobile artboard uses 26 and
       has no controls row at all. */
    --gap-section: 32px;
    --gap-section-m: 26px;
    --gap-tiles: 24px;
    --gap-tiles-m: 16px;
    --gap-tile-inner: 16px;

    /* Tile. 407px on the 1440 artboard, 260px on the 375 one — both fixed, neither derived. */
    --tile-w: 407px;
    --tile-w-m: 260px;
    --radius-tile: 32px;

    /* The two image crops alternate down the track. Carried as aspect-ratios rather than the
       artboard's raw pixel heights (312px / 373px) so the tile keeps its crop at ANY tile width
       — mobile reuses the same two ratios at 260px wide and lands on exactly 312 and 373. */
    --ratio-short: 260 / 312;
    --ratio-tall: 260 / 373;

    /* Controls (6704:28706). The buttons carry no fill or border on the artboard — 19px of
       padding around a 24px icon is the whole button, which also buys a 62px touch target. */
    --gap-controls: 32px;
    --gap-buttons: 8px;
    --button-p: 19px;
    --icon-size: 24px;
    --icon-stroke: 1.4;

    /* The progress rail is a 2px round-capped line. Figma draws it as a single stroke with a
       hard gradient stop — #262626 up to 21.6%, #DADADA after — i.e. it is a scrollbar THUMB,
       not decoration. So the fill below is computed from real scroll position by the JS, and
       21.6% is just the mock's own scroll offset. */
    --progress-h: 2px;

    /* Mobile lead-in: 40px on the artboard, against 80px on desktop. Expressed as a RATIO of the
       merchant's own padding rather than a flat 40px, so their slider still does something on a
       phone — the same idiom as the eleven other sections here. At the default 80 it lands on 40. */
    --pt-scale-m: 0.5;
  }
</style>

{%- liquid
  assign slide_count = 0
  for block in section.blocks
    if block.settings.image != blank or block.settings.text != blank
      assign slide_count = slide_count | plus: 1
    endif
  endfor
-%}

{%- if slide_count > 0 -%}
  <div
    class="story-slider"
    style="
      --bg: {{ section.settings.background_color }};
      --color: {{ section.settings.text_color }};
      --rail: {{ section.settings.rail_color }};
      --progress: {{ section.settings.progress_color }};
      --pt: {{ section.settings.padding_top }}px;
      --pb: {{ section.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
    "
  >
    <div class="story-slider__inner">
      {%- if section.settings.heading != blank -%}
        {%- comment -%} inline_richtext: already-safe HTML from Shopify — never escape it, or the merchant's italics arrive as visible tags. {%- endcomment -%}
        <h2 class="story-slider__heading">{{ section.settings.heading }}</h2>
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- comment -%}
        The track is a plain scroll container, not a JS-driven carousel. Keyboard, trackpad and
        touch already scroll it natively; the arrows below only nudge it, and the rail only
        reports where it is. That means the section still works with JS off — it degrades to the
        mobile behaviour, which IS the design at 375.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <ul class="story-slider__track" data-story-slider-track tabindex="0">
        {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
          {%- if block.settings.image == blank and block.settings.text == blank -%}
            {%- continue -%}
          {%- endif -%}

                    <li class="story-slider__tile" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
            <div class="story-slider__media story-slider__media--{{ block.settings.crop }}">
              {%- if block.settings.image != blank -%}
                {%- comment -%}
                  The tile's box is an aspect-ratio, and it is the SAME ratio on both breakpoints —
                  260/312 short, 260/373 tall, which is why the media wrapper can carry it as a
                  ratio rather than the artboard's pixel heights. So the CDN crop can follow the
                  block's own `crop` setting exactly, and one source serves every width. That is
                  unusual here and worth stating: no <picture> is needed on this section.

                  What the browser was doing instead, measured on Our Story at 1440 / DPR 2:

                    tile-3  box 407 x 488 -> delivered 814 x 1220, 20% of the height cropped away
                    tile-1  box 407 x 488 -> delivered 814 x 1016, 4% cropped away
                    tile-2  528 KB

                  The crop is the small half here — these sources are already near the box aspect.
                  The weight is the encode, and one tile is a genuine dead end. tile-2 is a dark,
                  grainy photograph, and noise is exactly what a lossy codec cannot throw away.
                  Measured on the delivered WebP at the 814x1168 desktop crop:

                    q75  388 KB  <- was      q60  341 KB
                    q70  375 KB              q55  324 KB
                    q65  353 KB              q50  302 KB (and the CDN flips to jpeg here)

                  25 points of quality buy 22%. Lighthouse asks this image to reach ~65 KB and no
                  setting on this filter gets near it. THAT ONE NEEDS A RE-ENCODED SOURCE UPLOADED
                  TO FILES — the original is 2.24 MB — and no markup change substitutes for it.

                  70 for every tile, png and jpg alike. They sit side by side in one track, so a
                  visitor would see two of them crisper than the others if the branches disagreed.

                  png takes format: 'webp', not 'jpg'. jpg would flatten alpha; webp keeps it and
                  still accepts quality, and it is the only reason a png is compressible at all
                  here — tile-1 and tile-4 were shipping at full weight before this, 76 KB and
                  124 KB, now 35 KB and 58 KB.

                  tile-1 and tile-4 are png. Both are colour-type 2 — no alpha channel at all, so
                  there is nothing for jpg to flatten — but that is a fact about TODAY'S artwork,
                  not about the setting, and a merchant can swap either for a png that does have
                  alpha. So the extension is read off the URL and a png keeps the crop and skips
                  the recompression, rather than being converted on an assumption.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                {%- liquid
                  comment
                    Base 1221 = the top of the ladder, not the size of any box. `image_tag` drops
                    every `widths:` entry wider than the base url without saying so, and a base of
                    814 quietly capped the srcset there. The base is only the `src` fallback.
                  endcomment
                  if block.settings.crop == 'tall'
                    assign tile_h = 1752
                  else
                    assign tile_h = 1465
                  endif

                  assign tile_ext = block.settings.image | image_url: width: 1 | split: '?' | first | split: '.' | last | downcase
                  if tile_ext == 'gif'
                    assign tile_src = block.settings.image | image_url: width: 1221, height: tile_h, crop: 'center'
                  elsif tile_ext == 'png'
                    assign tile_src = block.settings.image | image_url: width: 1221, height: tile_h, crop: 'center', format: 'webp', quality: 70
                  else
                    assign tile_src = block.settings.image | image_url: width: 1221, height: tile_h, crop: 'center', quality: 70
                  endif
                -%}
                {{
                  tile_src
                  | image_tag:
                    loading: 'lazy',
                    widths: '260, 320, 407, 520, 620, 720, 814, 960, 1221',
                    sizes: '(max-width: 768px) 260px, 407px',
                    alt: block.settings.image_alt,
                    class: 'story-slider__image'
                }}
              {%- endif -%}
            </div>

            {%- if block.settings.text != blank -%}
              {%- comment -%} richtext: already safe HTML from Shopify — never escape it. {%- endcomment -%}
              <div class="story-slider__caption">{{ block.settings.text }}</div>
            {%- endif -%}
          </li>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </ul>

      {%- comment -%}
        Controls exist only on the desktop artboard — the mobile one scrolls natively with no
        rail and no arrows, so the CSS hides this whole row at ≤768px rather than inventing a
        mobile treatment for it.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="story-slider__controls">
        <div class="story-slider__rail">
          <span class="story-slider__progress" data-story-slider-progress></span>
        </div>

        <div class="story-slider__buttons">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="story-slider__button"
            data-story-slider-prev
            aria-label="{{ section.settings.prev_label | escape }}"
          >
            {%- comment -%} Icon/Outline/arrow-narrow-left, pasted verbatim from the Figma export;
              only stroke #333333 -> currentColor, so it follows --color. {%- endcomment -%}
            <svg class="story-slider__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
<path d="M7 8L3 12L7 16M3 12L21 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
</svg>
          </button>

          <button
            type="button"
            class="story-slider__button"
            data-story-slider-next
            aria-label="{{ section.settings.next_label | escape }}"
          >
            <svg class="story-slider__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
<path d="M17 16L21 12L17 8M21 12L3 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
</svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
{%- endif -%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Story slider",
  "tag": "section",
  "settings": [
    { "type": "header", "content": "Content" },
    { "type": "inline_richtext", "id": "heading", "label": "Heading", "default": "Where it all began...." },
    { "type": "text", "id": "prev_label", "label": "Previous button label (screen readers only)", "default": "Previous slide" },
    { "type": "text", "id": "next_label", "label": "Next button label (screen readers only)", "default": "Next slide" },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Colors" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "background_color", "label": "Background", "default": "#FFFCF4" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "text_color", "label": "Text color", "default": "#333333" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "rail_color", "label": "Scroll rail", "default": "#DADADA" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "progress_color", "label": "Scroll progress", "default": "#262626" },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Spacing" },
    { "type": "range", "id": "padding_top", "min": 0, "max": 120, "step": 4, "unit": "px", "label": "Padding top", "default": 80 },
    { "type": "range", "id": "padding_bottom", "min": 0, "max": 120, "step": 4, "unit": "px", "label": "Padding bottom", "default": 0 }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "slide",
      "name": "Slide",
      "settings": [
        { "type": "image_picker", "id": "image", "label": "Image" },
        { "type": "text", "id": "image_alt", "label": "Image alt text" },
        {
          "type": "richtext",
          "id": "text",
          "label": "Caption",
          "info": "Bold the opening phrase — the artboard sets it in Public Sans Bold and the rest in Medium.",
          "default": "<p><strong>Our story began in 2024,</strong><br>with our founder Reuven Sherman setting out to find the very best in natural sleep.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "select",
          "id": "crop",
          "label": "Image crop",
          "info": "The artboard alternates the two down the track.",
          "default": "short",
          "options": [
            { "value": "short", "label": "Short (260:312)" },
            { "value": "tall", "label": "Tall (260:373)" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "max_blocks": 12,
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Story slider",
      "blocks": [
        { "type": "slide", "settings": { "crop": "short" } },
        { "type": "slide", "settings": { "crop": "tall" } },
        { "type": "slide", "settings": { "crop": "short" } },
        { "type": "slide", "settings": { "crop": "tall" } }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
